refactor: migrate datasets for an old running instance (#8)

In this PR, we include the automatic migration workflow.

1. Create the new `ar.datasets` index
2. Reindex documents from the old `.rubrix.datasets-v0` (if any) index into `ar.datasets`
3. Scan every document in `.rubrix.datasets-v0` and create an alias matching the new argilla dataset records index naming convention. (`ar.dataset.<dataset_id>`)

The configured namespace will be used for the migration. So, if a namespace `A` is defined (`ARGILLA_NAMESPACE`), all actions in the migration, will be related to that workspace.

Refs: https://github.com/recognai/Team/issues/42
(cherry picked from commit c2c9191907b72a2df77d52e09edeb223b1a7bd99)

Also:
- Enable migration by environment variable ARGILLA_ENABLE_MIGRATION
- Delete alias when delete a dataset

refactor: Collection of changes, primarily regarding test suite and its coverage (#1702)

* test: Speed up slow test

On my device, api.init() takes 2.5 seconds per execution. Running it 1000 times does not make the test any more robust than e.g. 20, so I've made this change to speed up the total test suite execution.\n\nIt is however noteworthy that this test is so slow on my device...

* test: Ignore dtype on some tests due to failures on my device

The np.array([...]) call inferred the values to int32, while the expected_summary calls inferred the 'correct' and 'incorrect' columns to int64. This caused test failures.\n\nFurthermore, I stopped using the deprecated pandas.util.testing.assert_frame_equal, and moved to pandas.testing.assert_frame_equal fully

* test: Exclude code blocks from coverage that are not normally tested

See https://buildmedia.readthedocs.org/media/pdf/coverage/coverage-5.0a3/coverage.pdf for the inspiration of this list.

* refactor: Remove unreachable code in rb.copy()

datasets_api.copy_dataset calls _build_response, which either returns a Responseif status_code == 200, and otherwise calls handle_response_error, which always throws an error. With other words, the only way for response = datasets_api.copy_dataset to be filled is if the status_code == 200. As such, it will never be 409.\n\nNote also that the RuntimeError is now implemented via AlreadyExistsApiError, which is tested via tests/client/test_api.py::test_dataset_copy.

* test: Add test for the background parameter on rb.log()

* test: Update tests to use 	ext instead of inputs

Only with strings. This is to prepare for the upcoming deprecation. The only case that was left is the case that tests whether the deprecation warning is shown correctly.

* test: Resolve DeprecationWarning: invalid escape sequence

* fix: Add missing space between dot and the start of the new sentence

* Update tests/client/test_init.py
